ji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-08T14:29:35.000Z","msg":"我每次都趁自己隻巴西唔留意先偷摸佢"},{"pid":"c5045c4776e3925c598189c3fd485f211d3c76f5","tid":2146370,"uid":87337,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"003c7eabfcd555e18966955d333e2634236c7283","tid":2146370,"uid":189109,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2020-08-08T14:11:23.000Z","msg":"我隻龜唔鍾意<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/drum.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/drum.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/drum.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-08T15:39:35.000Z","msg":"我以前細個養龜<br />\n試過摸佢但俾佢咬<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/cry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n勁傷心<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/cry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"f204e866cd48f44b49e53f3934d8f8fe0c6a401e","tid":2146370,"uid":157508,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"quote":{"pid":"3ee356c122148b5896887dc06476d8aff55f0b6c","tid":2146370,"uid":196625,"like":11,"dislike":0,"score":11,"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2020-08-08T13:53:53.000Z","msg":"因為R 唔到"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-08-08T17:32:22.000Z","msg":"啱啊<br />\n<br />\nFor instance, petting a cat or a dog on the head gives the animal attention, which it might crave, said Dr. Nicholas Dodman, a professor emeritus at the Cummings School of Veterinary Medicine at Tufts University. Moreover, it's difficult for cats and dogs to touch the tops of their heads with their paws, and it's impossible for them to lick it with their tongues. [20 Weird Dog and Cat Behaviors Explained by Science]<br />\n<br />\n&quot;It's a relatively inaccessible area that you can reach for them, so you're doing them a favor in that sense,&quot; Dodman told Live Science.<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.livescience.com/59521-why-cats-dogs-like-head-scratches.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2F59521-why-cats-dogs-like-head-scratches.html&d=Ieu1u4uPL9fG%2BDPeYXLiW4PST22DtV%2BdF%2FIIxhOvvTQ%3D&h=0dfbe79